2}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater}, {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}{SO}$_{\textrm{2}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater}, and {CO} from 2013 to 2017 of approximately 34\&thinsp;\%, 24\&thinsp;\%, 17\&thinsp;\%, 68\&thinsp;\%, and 33\&thinsp;\%, respectively, after meteorological correction. The marked decrease in {PM}{\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}$_{\textrm{2.5}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater} and {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}{SO}$_{\textrm{2}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater} is largely attributable to a reduction in coal combustion. Our results indicate that the action plan has been highly effective in reducing the primary pollution emissions and improving air quality in Beijing. The action plan offers a successful example for developing air quality policies in other regions of China and other developing countries.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
