e stringent future{\textless}span id="page8954"/{\textgreater} emission controls provide a large reduction in both surface {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}O$_{\textrm{3}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater} concentrations and {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}O$_{\textrm{3}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater} radiative forcing. The parameterisation provides a simple tool to highlight the different impacts and associated uncertainties of local and hemispheric emission control strategies on both surface air quality and the near-term climate forcing by tropospheric {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}O$_{\textrm{3}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater}.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
